article.description: UC Santa Barbara romps past UC Irvine, 80-60
article.headline: UC Santa Barbara romps past UC Irvine, 80-60
article.linkText: UC Santa Barbara romps past UC Irvine, 80-60
article.story: SANTA BARBARA, Calif. -- Alan Williams pumped in 26 points as UC Santa Barbara romped past UC Irvine, 80-60 Thursday night. The Gauchos built a 10-point lead in the first half, then padded it down the stretch to pull even with the Anteaters atop the Big West Conference standings at 4-2. UC Santa Barbara started the game on a 13-0 run, capped by Zalmico Harmon's 3-pointer three minutes into the game. Williams with 10 of 17 from the field and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead UC Santa Barbara (13-6, 4-2 Big West), which shot 49 percent from the field (24 of 49) and held a 41-33 edge on the boards. Taran Brown added 16 points and six boards for the Gauchos. Luke Nelson scored 26 points to lead UC Irvine (13-9, 4-2), hitting 6 of 15 from long range while the Anteaters struggled from the field, hitting just 20 of 56 shots (35.7 percent).
